      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey, i'm working on a shopify theme and im having a weird issue with the product template. on desktop it looks fine but when i check it on my phone the product image is totally overlapping the title and description. cant tell if its a padding issue or something with the media queries. \n\nhere is the css for the product section:\n\n.product-container {\n  display: flex;\n  flex-direction: row;\n  gap: 20px;\n}\n\n.product-media {\n  width: 50%;\n}\n\n.product-info {\n  width: 50%;\n}\n\n@media only screen and (max-width: 767px) {\n  .product-container {\n    display: block;\n  }\n  .product-media, .product-info {\n    width: 100%;\n  }\n}\n\nthe liquid looks standard too. can u see what might be causing the overlap?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Ah, it seems like the issue is due to the flexbox layout not behaving as expected on smaller screens. In the desktop view, the product image and the title/description are likely spaced apart nicely, but when you switch to a smaller screen, the flex container's children are trying to occupy the full width, causing the overlap.\n\nTo fix this, you might want to consider adjusting the flex properties or using media queries to ensure that the product image and the title/description don't overlap. For example, you could try adding a margin to the product-info class in your media query:\n\n@media only screen and (max-width: 767px) {\n  .product-container {\n    display: block;\n  }\n  .product-media, .product-info {\n    width: 100%;\n  }\n  .product-info {\n    margin-left: 20px;\n  }\n}\n\nThis should give you some extra space between the product image and the title/description on smaller screens. Keep in mind that there might be other factors at play, so feel free to experiment and tweak the CSS until you find the perfect solution!",
      "source": "target",
