      "content": "I see, it sounds like the issue might be more complex than just adjusting the margin. It's possible that the z-index isn't the problem, but rather the way the flexbox is handling the space between the elements. \n\nOne thing you could try is adjusting the gap property in the .product-container class. This property controls the space between the flex items, and increasing it might help prevent the elements from overlapping. For example:\n\n.product-container {\n  display: flex;\n  flex-direction: row;\n  gap: 40px; // Increased from 20px\n}\n\nAnother option is to try using the flex-wrap property in the .product-container class. This property allows the flex items to wrap onto multiple lines if there isn't enough space in the container. By setting it to wrap, you can ensure that the product image and the title/description don't overlap. For example:\n\n.product-container {\n  display: flex;\n  flex-direction: row;\n  gap: 20px;\n  flex-wrap: wrap; // Added this line\n}\n\nYou could also try using the flex-basis property in the .product-media and .product-info classes. This property controls the initial size of the flex items, and by setting it to a percentage, you can",
